##Visiting hotels in Wuhan: This is not a polluted area

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Reporter, Liao Yan, intern, Zhao Yumeng, Wuhan, China

"It's a lucky door. "

Across the hallway, Machen pointed to Elevator 4, the elevator through which most of the people who had been in close contact since the end of the quarantine period had left. Those who had gone down the stairs, he said, had developed symptoms that required a referral, and in the worst cases, a diagnosis.

Machen's isolation point is a "retirement" hotel in the European town of Wuhan's Hannan District Green Belt, about an hour's drive from the city center.

A few days earlier, it had been requisitioned to isolate "close contacts of newly diagnosed patients with coronary pneumonia. "

The health clinic where Machen worked took over the second, third and fourth floors of the BCC hotel, with 19 rooms on each floor, all 57 of which were requisitioned for use as BCC isolation rooms.

"It's basically 'one in, one out, ' " Chen, who is in charge of medical care at the isolation point, told The Paper news www.thepaper.cn  that under the requirements of "every possible remedy" and "every possible remedy" , the two quarantines they've taken over at the health facility will be full in two or three days.

From 3 February to 13 February, their close observation point received a total of 66 close contacts. As of February 15, seven patients had been referred for suspected new crown pneumonia.

In the week since they took over the isolation site for suspected new crown pneumonia patients, more than a dozen confirmed cases of the disease have been transferred to designated hospitals for treatment as a result of accelerated nucleic acid testing and clinical diagnosis.

What Chen and Machen hope is that more of their close contacts will be able to walk through the "lucky door" .

A condemned hotel

On February 2, the COVID-19 issued a notice on strengthening the isolation, treatment and management of patients with fever, suspected patients with fever and close contacts. The notice proposed that cities, states and counties should immediately requisition resources such as hotels, hotels and guest houses that are relatively independent in location, have little impact on the surrounding environment, and are equipped with water, electricity, clean and sewage protection, and rapidly transform them into centralized isolation points.

On the afternoon of February 13th The Paper drove an hour through two checkpoints to visit a condemned hotel, the Florida health and Wellness Hotel, for the treatment of close contacts.

The hotel's second, third and fourth floors, each floor 19 rooms, a total of 57 rooms were requisitioned.

Before entering the hotel, there were two security guards at the door, one with an infrared thermometer in his hand and the other with a watering can filled with alcohol.

"hold on. " The security guard stopped a man who was about to enter the hotel. He held an infrared thermometer to the man's forehead and it said his temperature was "36.5 c. ". Another guard, holding a watering can, sprayed alcohol on the man and on the soles of his shoes. The man was then allowed into the hotel.

Kenneth Ma, the hotel's chef de cuisine, also took on the temporary job of dispatching the hotel. Kenneth Ma and his colleagues will be wearing protective clothing and N95 masks. Some of their colleagues did not wear goggles because they lacked protective equipment such as protective gloves and goggles.

Several colleagues sat at the front desk, walkie talkies in their hands, and from time to time the voices of the medical staff in the quarantined area spoke to them about their patients'needs before they were sent to the buffer zone.

On January 30, the hotel asked its staff to volunteer for the outbreak service, Kenneth Ma said. The original hotel has 26 employees, due to the closure of the city, many staff in the provinces can not return to work, only 12 staff at present. In order to ensure the normal operation of the hotel, the staff did not shift system, the basic 24-hour overload working state.

Upon receiving the notification, they also adjusted the doors and windows of the hotel in accordance with the requirements of those in close contact with NCP. The doors leading to the steps are bolted and can only be opened by staff in one direction. "It's to keep the ciphers from going anywhere, " Kenneth Ma said.

On 3 February, the hotel began receiving close contacts with new crown pneumonia.

Kenneth Ma said the hotel only caters for close contacts of patients with newly diagnosed pneumonia. Since February 3, the hotel has received 66 close contacts with new pneumonia, and three people have left the hotel because of the expiration of the isolation period, another three people were sent to Wuhan People's Hospital with fever and have been diagnosed as having new crown pneumonia. As of February 13, the hotel currently has 48 close contacts, with three more coming in the evening.

Referring to whether there were any difficulties in purchasing supplies during the epidemic, Kenneth Ma said that it was a bit difficult to purchase supplies because of the closure of the city. The hotel had to feed 100 people every day and the demand was high, but it was working hard to overcome the shortage of supplies, as far as possible to ensure a variety of dishes, ensure that every meal is two meat two vegetables, a soup.

Hotel staff is mainly responsible for close contact and medical staff catering and logistics.

Before the hotel receives the secret receiver, the hotel has already completed the related daily necessities in the room, also has cooperated with the government to make the related plan. Patients with fever will contact the community and be sent to Hannan District People's Hospital.

After the hotel's first confirmed case was reported on Feb. 6, staff members began to worry about whether they might be infected, hotel employee Chomez said. One of the staff is in the breast-feeding period, the child is only 6 months, think the child can only see the child through video, but in order to fight the epidemic, in an effort to adjust the state, stick to the Post. "Some employees are a little emotional and a little scared, and sometimes they come to me in the middle of the night to talk, " Chomez said.

The man who was delivering the dinner

One Room each

Before entering the exclusion zone, you will need to travel through a buffer zone.

The hotel's interior is a u shaped structure, with a separate area for close contacts and staff to prevent cross contamination of health care workers.

Each of the quarantined room door are affixed with an information sheet, which will be marked with name, sex, age, past history, isolation time and other information, in order to facilitate medical staff to check body temperature, communication.

There is a two-tier table at the door of the room, with meals on the first floor and garbage on the second. Breakfast is generally steamed bread, porridge, eggs, milk and other meals, lunch, dinner can be guaranteed two meat a vegetable, but also with some fruit, such as oranges, apples.

Cai Jie, who lives at the end of the corridor, is one of those being quarantined. She was wearing a rose-colored mask that covered most of her face, but still showed the beauty between her eyebrows.

Cai Jie's mother was diagnosed with new crown pneumonia, and she and her father checked into the isolation hotel.

Cai Jie, her mother is Hannan District People's Hospital, a nurse, in the hospital work infected with new coronavirus pneumonia. After her diagnosis, on 4 February, the community informed her that she had come with her father to be quarantined, and that she had no fever, cough or other symptoms, and that she was being treated at the hospital, where she was in an improved condition.

"My mother had a fever for five days at home, and the first CT scan of her lungs showed no abnormalities, " Cai said, adding that it took a while for her mother to be diagnosed after another nucleic acid test and a CT scan.

"I am worried about my mother, after all, she is alone in the hospital, " Cai Jie said.

Cai Jie is a junior high school music teacher, due to online teaching, she needs to prepare daily classes in the hotel, prepared for the weekly online teaching.

Cai Jie lived in a standard, two-bed, the bed is opposite the window, her father lived next door. "When I stay in my room and don't work, I watch TV shows, " Cai Jie said. She cleans the room herself, scrubbing the floor every three days. She also introduced that every day there are staff members do disinfection processing, they put garbage in the door, every day someone came to clean up.

At first, Cai Jie is still very afraid of new coronavirus pneumonia, but now her mood has calmed down. "I live in a good environment here now, the medical staff will take my temperature twice a day, and the hotel staff will take care of the Three Meals a Day, " said Cai Jie, but she is worried about her mother because she is alone in the hospital.

According to the management requirements is a room per person, isolated to avoid cross-infection.

"But the reality is that there are older people and younger people, and that's not entirely avoidable, so sometimes you need someone else. We have an 85-year-old man here, who's not very good at taking care of himself. In this case, we can only allow his grandson to go up to take care of the old man. But we also have very strict requirements for them, such as wearing a mask even inside the room, taking care for too long and not too often to avoid cross-infection,"Chen said.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A small table at the door of a room

24-hour-a-day paramedic

"Is this a contaminated area? "

"No, we call it the observation area, " explained nurse Machen. They are just close contacts, and if it is called the "contamination area, " it will have a psychological effect on them.

Machen, a nurse at the same hospital, had also been working for half a month.

Machen, who was on duty today, had been in quarantine two hours earlier. Machen, wearing a white hazmat suit and double gloved gloves, was visible in the dimly lit hallway. Her goggles had fogged up and she was speaking out of breath. Sweat was visible on her forehead through the goggles.

"[ the suit ] is full of water and it's raining, " gasped Machen, as she prepared to take her contact's temperature.

Machen, a 55 year old former SARS fighter, is in her 31st year as a nurse. "This epidemic is a protracted battle, " she said

They make rounds twice a day, with a four hour shift staffed by a doctor and a nurse on a 24 hour basis, Machen said.

Each day, Machen said, they take the temperature of their contacts at 9 a.m. and 3 p.m. and watch them for changes. If anything goes wrong, they immediately contact the community workers to arrange for the contacts to be transferred to a fever clinic.

On the drug side, they now offer ciphers Lianhua Qingwen capsules. In addition, an appropriate amount of COVID-191 decoction is given according to the situation of close contacts. Once the 14-day quarantine period is over, a close contact with stable vital signs can be transferred out of the quarantine area.

Speaking of which, Machen walked down the hallway to the door of an elevator. She pointed to the No. 4 Elevator and said, "this is a lucky door. "

The elevator is used to get out when the quarantine expires, Machen said, while people who go down the stairs may have symptoms that require a referral, and in severe cases, a diagnosis. "We want more and more of our ciphers to get out of here, not down the stairs, " Machen said.

Nurse may was holding a walkie-talkie at all times. "We have 14 walkie-talkies. We send messages from inside and outside the walkie-talkie quarantine zone, " Machen said. If something happens to the receiver, they can call the doctor on duty at any time.

With bloodshot eyes and a medical mask and a blue head covering, Chen was in the room with a walkie talkie, docking work with colleagues. "I sent them to the front line with my own hands, " he said. "I'm always grateful to them. The only thing I can do is protect them. "

Chen Qiao said that on January 7, his hospital began to do "pre-examination and triage" , responsible for the transfer of fever patients. Then in the "should receive" , "should cure" under the request, their hospital took over the two isolation points, one is close to the isolation point, one is suspected of new pneumonia patients isolation point, two or three days to full.

Chen Qiao rests for 3 hours or 5 hours at most. "Like me, my colleagues stay up almost every night, " Chen said with a sigh.

Chen Qiao introduced, for close contact and suspected new pneumonia patients, is now a file each person, there is a past history, serious patients, will focus on. One close contact, if there is fever patients, they will arrange fever patients transferred to Hannan District People's Hospital, Yaxin General Hospital and other hospitals.

In addition, in order to take care of their emotions, close contact isolation point corresponding arrangements for the psychological doctor, close contact for psychological counseling.

They also need to keep an eye on the psychology of their contacts, says Machen. She recalled an 85-year-old man whose wife had died, and whose daughter said she would keep secrets from him, so they would pay special attention to his psychological changes during rounds.

When it comes to problems at work, Chen said, they will encounter secret receivers who do not understand the work of the medical staff, who feel that they may have been isolated for a long time, plus the active area is only in their own room, which makes them a little irritable. "sometimes there are misunderstandings between close contacts and medical staff. Fortunately, it is basically a verbal conflict and it is resolved in time. I still believe that most people understand our work, " Chen said.

As recently as February 12, seven of the ciphers in the BCC had been released from quarantine, but seven more were immediately admitted. Now it's basically "one in, one out. ". As of February 13, a total of 11 close contacts had returned home from isolation.

At 6 p.m. , Machen took off her protective clothing and mask, leaving a deep impression on her face. "My face is more fleshy, so I leave marks easily, " she joked to herself. Chen Qiao also ushered in a new task, their hospital needs to take over a quarantine point, he is still trying to solve the problem of staffing.

The ciphers in quarantine, they're waiting out the quarantine. After 14 days, some people were released from quarantine and returned home from the elevator of Lucky Gate 4, while others were transported to the next location in a transfer vehicle for further testing.
